<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="44">
There is little reason to consider 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26110" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">Brachymyrmex heeri</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239645" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex aphidicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphidicola">B. aphidicola</taxonomicName>
as conspecific, as both species are locally sympatric and morphologically distinct in eastern Paraguay. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239645" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex aphidicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphidicola">Brachymyrmex aphidicola</taxonomicName>
is one of the most abundant ground and litter nesting ant species in Paraguayan forests. 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26110" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">Brachymyrmex heeri</taxonomicName>
is more rarely collected, the two nest records I have from Paraguay are both arboreal. The two species are easily separated by the pubescence on gastric tergite 1 (= abd. tergite 3), with the pubescence dense on 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26110" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">B. heeri</taxonomicName>
and sparse on 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239645" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex aphidicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphidicola">B. aphidicola</taxonomicName>
. Santschi’s type of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:148046" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri fallax Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="heeri" subSpecies="fallax">B. heeri fallax</taxonomicName>
(NHMB, examined) falls within the range of variation exhibited by 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239645" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex aphidicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphidicola">B. aphidicola</taxonomicName>
in Paraguay and is synonymized here. It is worth mentioning here that Paraguayan specimens of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26110" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">B. heeri</taxonomicName>
are a close match, in both the worker and queen castes, to Forel’s types of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26110" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex heeri Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="heeri">B. heeri</taxonomicName>
(MHNG examined) described from an introduced population in Switzerland (Forel 1874).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="44">
Given the notoriously poor taxonomic state of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:2407" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Brachymyrmex</taxonomicName>
and the ubiquity of 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:239645" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Brachymyrmex" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Brachymyrmex aphidicola" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aphidicola">B. aphidicola</taxonomicName>
in the region, there may well exist an older name for this species. A thorough taxonomic revision of this genus is sorely needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
